    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Target Chooses Arnold for 3 Chains</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Target Corp names Arnold Communications to handle first corproate branding campaign for department store chains Dayton's, Marshall Field's and Hudson's; spending estimated at $40 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Target Corporation in Minneapolis has named Arnold Communications in Boston to handle the first corporate branding campaign for three department store chains, Dayton's, Marshall Field's and Hudson's. Spending was estimated at $40 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Target Corporation in Minneapolis has named Arnold Communications in Boston to handle the first corporate branding campaign for three department store chains, Dayton's, Marshall Field's and Hudson's. Spending was estimated at $40 million.</p>
        <p>The decision, which came without a review, does not involve the Target chain of discount stores.</p>
        <p>Arnold is part of Snyder Communications, which has agreed to be acquired by Havas Advertising.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
